Surely you don't need to fully qualify anything?
```suggestion
    Iic a * Iic b âŠ† Iic (a * b) := by
```
I think these are easier to read as `(Â· * Â·)` etc, but it's up to you

Can we have a TODO for the analogous lemmas in the generality of `mul_le_mul` rather than `mul_le_mul'`? I need these for the exponential ramsey project, so I don't mind PRing them myself later. But of course feel free to add them here anyway.
Done. I moved all my existing lemmas to occupy the primed names.

I think you should unprime them and have `\_0` or `_of_pos`/`_of_nonneg` for the other ones instead. I'm trying to deprecate priming ordered monoid lemmas (it leads to a confusing mess of a naming convention) and I would like there not to be more lemma names to fix.
I'd rather optimize for current consistency rather than eventual consistency that may be never be reached.
Well yeah, if you work against it...
This is a very real thing that is going to happen really soon, btw. I have a gitpod with 150 files changed in it to fix one collection of lemma names, and `mul_le_mul'` will be my next batch.
At this point me reverting the names now is no easier than you doing so in your chain of PRs, and thematically the de-priming makes much more sense there.
